question: Lily has 3 jars of frosting in her kitchen cabinet. Each jar of frosting can decorate 14 muffins. Lily wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her frosting. If each rack holds 6 muffins, how many racks worth of muffins should she bake?
answer:
She has enough frosting for 3 * 14 = <<3*14=42>>42 muffins.
She needs 42 / 6 = <<42/6=7>>7 racks to bake all of the muffins.
#### 7
